A7169 &Cx1f; ttf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FRONTPAGE-UPDATE-NYT &LR;      07-02 0121
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FRONTPAGE-UPDATE-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors: The following story is being added to The New York
Times front page. We will move story by 1 a.m., ET.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-FIRES (Miami) _ Florida officials evacuated more than 15,000
in the Ormond Beach area late on Wednesday as dozens of wild fires
whipped by high winds started up in the afternoon and burned dozens
of homes and commercial buildings. Officials said commercial areas
here and Daytona Beach are threatened, and late reports said 30
homes and several cars were destroyed in Brevard County to the
south near Mims. The fire and smoke forced the closing of all major
roads leading into Ormond Beach, a city of about 35,000 people, and
forced the closing of I-95 to Jacksonville.
</P>
</TEXT>
