<HEADLINE>
UZI SPREE IN BAR HURTS NO ONE BUT GUNMAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BHAVNA MISTRY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LANCASTER, Calif. &UR;  &LR; -- A trailer park resident in a dispute with
the park's manager shot up a neighboring bar with an Uzi submachine
gun before being subdued by patrons, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffery Anderson entered the Del Sur Gardens Bar, 9020 W. Ave.
J, shortly after 4 p.m. Tuesday, ordered a drink and got into an
argument with the park manager. He left, but soon returned armed
and wearing a camouflage jacket, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He walked in and told everyone to leave but (the park
manager),'' bartender Lori Nard said. ``Then he fired two shots
into the air and no one moved.''
</P>
<P>
   Anderson fired the weapon in a circular motion into the bar's
ceiling before Danny Farrell, 37, jumped up next to him, grabbed
the front end of the Uzi and pulled the gunman onto a pool table as
he continued to fire.
</P>
<P>
   Other patrons helped subdue Anderson until deputies arrived. He
was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder and was being held at
the Lancaster sheriff's station in lieu of $500,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Bar representatives said Anderson was angry with the trailer
park's manager, who he thought had been gossiping about him.
</P>
<P>
   Lancaster is about 60 miles north of downtown Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
