<P>
   SUMMER-BERRIES _ ORCHARD HILL, Ga. _ One of the surest ways of
telling a city kid from a country kid in the South is to ask
whether he's been blackberrying. City kids may not have heard the
berry used as a verb. Country kids have; they know it means long
pants and long sleeves, stickers and chiggers, inky fingertips and
pails of precious berries that catch the sunlight like cut glass.
(Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) NOT FOR USE BEFORE
SUNDAY, JULY 5. MOVED.
