<P>
   UNDATED _ As a tireless believer in the value of America's
two-party political system, I must say it was encouraging to watch
Texas Democrats whoop it up at their convention in San Antonio last
weekend. With no regard at all for polls that show Democratic
candidates in big trouble, party loyalists staged a terrific pep
rally in the Alamodome. They lit up the Alamo City as if they had
something to celebrate. It is not entirely clear what previously
untapped source of unbridled optimism might have fueled the
delegates' enthusiasm. But here's a guess: Al Gore. By BILL
THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
