   &UR; INVESTING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MILLIONAIRE-MANAGERS-BLOOM (New York) _ In another aspect of the
mutual fund industry boom, top fund managers are now being paid
millions of dollars a year by fund companies _ many times more than
they were earnings only a few years ago. By Jon Friedman.
</P>
<P>
   BEST-PERFORMERS-BLOOM (New York) _ The best performing U.S.
stocks in the first half of the year were either companies with
strong ties to the domestic economy or those whose products are
expected to fuel the economy of tomorrow.  &QL; 
By Philip Boroff.
</P>
<P>
   TOUGH-TIMES-PROTECTION-BLOOM (Boston) _ If you're concerned that
the run-up in U.S. stocks is over you may want to move some money
to these mutual funds with proven records of doing well in tough
times. By Tim Quinson.
</P>
<P>
   GRAYBEARDS-BLOOM (New York) _ Contrary to conventional wisdom,
young fund managers returned more to investors than wise and
seasoned veterans in recent years, according to a new survey. By
Jon Friedman.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL-WEALTH-FINANCIAL-FUNDS- (San Francisco) _ Mutual funds
focused on the financial industry have been the best performing
sector funds of the 1990s, but that run may be nearing an end. By
Sam Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETS-QUARTER-NYT (New York) _ The warnings that the bubble is
about to burst have been sounded each quarter for the past few
years, but investors in the stock market continue to ignore them.
And so far, despite a series of blows lately that were widely
expected to take the air out of the balloon, they have been right.
By David Barboza.
</P>
