   BELLSOUTH _ Officials of the union now bargaining with BellSouth
say they object to BellSouth's $50 million contract with three
temporary employment agencies. The deal is not covered by the
current contract, says the Communications Workers of America. The
CWA and BellSouth have until Aug. 8 (nd ch) to reach agreements on
contracts for six units now at the bargaining table. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 8 p.m.
