three-day weekend are contributing. The Nasdaq is off 20 points and
the Dow 30. Separately, the government reported slower U.S. job
growth in June, pushing the unemployment rate up to 4.5 percent
from a 28-year-low during the two previous months. (McNaughton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 8 p.m.
