<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Actress picks fun diversions
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FLAT ROCK, NC--
</P>
<P>
   We asked Atlanta actress Suzi Bass, who recently wrapped a
performance in ``The Sound of Music'' at the Flat Rock Playhouse,
to share a few of her favorite things about the area.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's such a wonderful place to be, a beautiful place,'' says
Bass, who has been with the Flat Rock company for four years, and
who has worked in Atlanta at the Alliance Theatre and Theatre in
the Square. ``These are five of my 100 favorite things. I could
come up with a bunch more.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Walks around the lake at the Carl Sandburg Home.
</P>
<P>
   -- Sunday brunch at the Highland Lake Inn.
</P>
<P>
   -- Window-shopping in downtown Hendersonville.
</P>
<P>
   -- Browsing at the Wrinkled Egg (gift shop) and the Secret
Garden (gardening shop).
</P>
<P>
   -- A short trip to Saluda to the Spinning Wheel Rug Outlet,
going to Pearson's Falls and then enjoying a cinnamon bun at the
Wildflower Bakery. Yum, yum.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
