Independent Counsel Kenneth Starr has marshaled more than 50
witnesses before a grand jury. But he also has another,
lesser-known Whitewater panel across the Potomac River in
Alexandria, Va. And it is there, some legal experts say, that Starr
might bring changes in the Monica Lewinsky case. By MARK HELM.
(Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   PR-STATEHOOD (Washington) _ Senate Republican leaders have good
news for manufacturers of American flags: You won't have to throw
out your inventory of 50-star flags any time soon. The U.S. Senate
isn't going to approve a procedure that could result in Puerto Rico
becoming the 51st state. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed)
</P>
