<P>
   MUTFUND-LIFE-STYLE (Undated) _ When mutual fund companies
started pushing so-called life-style and life-cycle funds, they
seemed like sure-fire hits: single funds that were meant to
simplify the decision-making process for befuddled investors.
Essentially, these funds would plunk an investor into a portfolio
with a mix of stocks, bonds and cash tailor-made to his investing
time horizon, eliminating the need to concern himself with
complicated issues like risk or asset allocation. The problem is
that investors, by and large, haven't warmed up to the idea. By
Abby Schultz.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-CLOSED-END (Undated) _ With closed-end funds developing
a reputation as a dysfunctional branch of the fund family tree,
shareholder activists have grown restive. That doesn't bother some
analysts, who feel that many such funds look like bargains as of
late. By Rick Gladstone.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-BENCHMARKS (Undated) _ So, how's your portfolio doing?
Good question. The fact is that you won't have a clue if you
measure your mutual fund's performance against the wrong benchmark.
Doing so can lead to Godzilla-size mistakes, like holding onto
losers or selling winners. By Noelle Knox.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-VANGUARD (Undated _ To hear John J. Brennan tell it,
there's really nothing much afoot at the Vanguard Group, the giant
fund company he heads. Vanguard, for example, definitely does not
intend to join the rush to build a financial services conglomerate,
he said. By Edward Wyatt.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-DOMESTIC (Undated) _ With the stock market as hot as a
firecracker, pushing the Standard &AMP; Poors 500 index to a record
high, why aren't mutual fund holders cheering? Because it is no fun
to incur losses in your fund holdings while the indexes race ever
higher. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-IAI-BALANCED (Undated) _ The IAI Balanced fund has
proven to be the best performer in the quarter of all stocks funds
trcked by the New York Timnes and the best domestic hybrid fund
over all. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-PORTFOLIOS (Undated) _ It has been one wild ride. Only
an unrepentant bull could have scooped up every dollar from the
red-hot stock market during the last five years as the Dow Jones
industrial average flirted with the 9,000 mark from the mid-3,000s.
Put simply, this time the theory of diversifying investments did
not work. Carefully balancing big stocks with smaller ones, or
American issues with international issues, was a waste of time.
Investors would have been better off sweeping their money into
Vanguard's S&AMP;P 500-stock index fund and going to the beach. By
Carole Gould.
</P>
<P>
   EARN
</P>
<P>
   EARN-MEDICAL-SAVINGS (Undated) _ An update on Medical Savings
Accounts, which started 18 months ago. A reinterview with some of
the people who signed up with high hopes. Not surprisingly, some
are quite disappointed. By Margaret O. Kirk.
</P>
<P>
   EARN-ABSENTS (Undated) _ Looking at how different companies have
combatted the persistent problem of absenteeism among employees,
i.e., Continental Airlines gives away Ford Explorers for six
month's perfect attendance. By Susan J. Wells. Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   EARN-INTERNS (Undated) _ There's a good deal to be said for
internships. Some say they give the intern a head start on a
permanent job. Then again, some interns, working for meager or no
wages, say they are a head start on slavery. By Lawrence Van
Gelder.
</P>
<P>
   SPEND
</P>
<P>
   SPEND-CAR-LEASE (Undated) _ A look at things to look out for
when returning a car coming off lease. By Andrea Adelson. Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   SPEND-BIZ-BOOKS (Undated) _ Deborah Stead reviews ``Burn Rate,''
by Michael Wolff. Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   Auto Stories: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-CORVETTE (Undated) _ No modern car on the American
road is more red-, white- and blue-blooded than the Chevrolet
Corvette. Introduced as a 1953 model, it was Americas first true,
mass-produced sportscar _ the United States' answer to the
pint-size roadsters that were being imported from Europe. And the
Corvette remains the only American sports car to stand the test of
time. A million-plus Corvettes have been built in more than four
decades, more than any other single sports car ever. By Michelle
Krebs.
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-CADILLAC (Undated) _ After decades in which Cadillac
represented the epitome of American luxury cars, it will start
selling its first truck this fall, a sport utility vehicle similar
to the Chevrolet Tahoe and GMC Yukon. By Leonard M. Apcar.
</P>
<P>
   Regular financial features:
</P>
<P>
   FUNDS-WATCH (funds) (Undated) _ A weekly report on changes in
mutual funds _ comings and goings among managers, changes in fees
and openings and closings. By Carole Gould.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-WATCH (watch) (New York) _ A look at developments in the
markets worldwide. By Gretchen Morgenson. Graphic.
