 &HT;    Where to call
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- Visitors heading to Florida should call ahead to
check road and weather conditions if they plan to visit an area hit
by fires and smoke. Visitors also might want to stop at Florida
Welcome stations to check on possible road closures or detours.
Here are numbers to call:
</P>
<P>
   Fla. tourism information: 1-888-246-8728
</P>
<P>
   Volusia County tourism information: 1-800-544-0415
</P>
<P>
   Florida Department of Transportation: 1-800-342-3557
</P>
<P>
   Florida's Space Coast Office of Tourism: 1-800-872-1969
</P>
<P>
   Florida Division of Emergency Management: 1-850-413-9900
</P>
<P>
   Florida welcome stations:
</P>
<P>
   I-75: Jennings, near Georgia border.
</P>
<P>
   I-95: Yulee, near Georgia border
</P>
<P>
   I-10: Pensacola, near Alabama border
</P>
<P>
   U.S. 231: Campbellton, near Alabama border
</P>
