<HEADLINE>
LIST OF THE TOP 100 FOREIGN FILMS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD NILSEN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   1.`` Children of Paradise'' (1945) Marcel Carne _ The French
Gone With the Wind. Everyone after the same woman. &QL; 
2.`` Rules of the Game'' (1939) Jean Renoir _ Infidelity in pre-war
France. Everyone after the same woman. &QL; 
3.`` Orphee'' (1949) Jean Cocteau _ French surrealist retells myth
with magical camera tricks. &QL; 
4.`` 8 1/2'' (1963) Federico Fellini _Italian fantasmagoria. &QL; 
5. ``Seven Samurai'' (1954) Akira Kurosawa _ Perfect samurai
movie. &QL; 
6.`` Battleship Potemkin'' (1925) Sergei Eisenstein _ 1905 Odessa
uprising and mutiny in Tsarist Russia. &QL; 
7. ``The Passion of Joan of Arc'' (1928) Carl Theodore Dreyer _ The
story of the French saint told in intense close-ups. &QL; 
8.`` Ran'' (1985) Kurosawa _ Japanese ``King Lear''. &QL; 
9. ``The Blue Angel'' (1930) Josef von Sternberg _ Obsession,
degradation, sex in pre-Hitler Germany. &QL; 
10.`` Andrei Rublev'' (1966) Andre Tarkovsky _ Cryptic and
beautiful film about art and faith in a brutal world. &QL; 
11.`` Rashomon'' (1950) Kurosawa _ He-said, she-said in medieval
Japan, looks at nature of truth. &QL; 
12.`` Grand Illusion'' (1937) Renoir _ Prison bust in WWI. &QL; 
13.`` Amarcord'' (1974) Fellini _ A nostalgic film memoir. &QL; 
14. ``La Strada'' (1954) Fellini _ Italian circus strong-man
Anthony Quinn takes wife, loses same. &QL; 
15.`` Seventh Seal'' (1957) Ingmar Bergman _ Death checkmates the
Swedish knight during the Plague Years. &QL; 
16.`` Wild Strawberries'' (1957) Bergman _ Old Swedish doctor takes
a road trip through the past to examine his life. &QL; 
17.`` Jules and Jim'' (1961) Francois Truffaut _ Two guys, one
girl. You do the math. The delights of French bohemia. &QL; 
18. ``Abel Gance's Napoleon'' (1927) Abel Gance _ The great film
biography, recently restored. &QL; 
19.`` Ikiru'' (1952) Kurosawa _ Dying old man finds purpose to his
life by beating the bureaucracy. &QL; 
20.`` Cabinet of Dr. Caligari'' (1919) Robert Wiene _ Expressionist
ur-horror tale is a silent classic. &QL; 
21.`` La Dolce Vita'' (1960) Fellini _ Unforgetable images. We have
met the anomie and it is us. &QL; 
22.`` The Bicycle Thief'' (1949) Vittorio de Sica _ Neo-Realist
classic about bike messenger who loses his wheels. &QL; 
23.`` 400 Blows'' (1959) Truffaut _ French borstal boy. &QL; 
24.`` Fanny and Alexander'' (1983) Bergman _ Theater family
readjusts to life with strict preacher step-father. &QL; 
25. ``Breathless'' (1959) Jean-Luc Goddard _ New Wave punk on the
lam, with Jean Seberg. &QL; 
26.`` L'Avventura'' (1960) Michelangelo Antonioni _ Existential
mystery about a woman who disappears on an island. &QL; 
27. ``The Conformist'' (1971) Bernardo Bertolucci _ The psychology
of fascism in Mussolini's Italy. &QL; 
28. ``Day for Night'' (1973) Truffaut _ Sweet-natured film about
shenanigans on the set of a ``B'' movie. &QL; 
29.`` Cries and Whispers'' (1972) Bergman _ Who loves the dying
woman? The sisters or the nurse? &QL; 
30.`` Alexander Nevsky'' (1938) Eisenstein _ Battle on the ice. &QL; 
31.`` Persona'' (1966) Bergman _ Burning psychological study of
mute actress and her nurse. &QL; 
32.`` Ugetsu Monogatari'' (1953) Kenji Mizoguchi _ Two brothers and
ambition in medieval Japan. &QL; 
33.`` Wings of Desire'' (1988) Wim Wenders _ Angel hears poetry of
life and is seduced. &QL; 
34.`` Metropolis'' (1926) Fritz Lang _ The future choreographed as
machinery. &QL; 
35.`` Nosferatu'' (1922) F.W. Murnau _ The original ``Dracula''. &QL; 
36.`` Le Jour se Leve'' (1939) Carne _ Jean Gabin as a murderer
waiting for the police to come. &QL; 
37.`` The Last Laugh'' (1924) Murnau _ Devastating, brilliant
silent film with no title cards about age and humiliation. &QL; 
38.`` Solaris'' (1972) Tarkovsky _ Russian director's answer to
``2001: A Space'' ``Odyssey.'' &QL; 
39.`` Dr. Mabuse, Gambler'' (1922) Lang _ Two-part allegory of Nazi
evil with Rudolf Klein-Rogge. &QL; 
40.`` Viridiana'' (1970) Luis Bunuel _ Innocence corrupted, with
the beggars' ``Last Supper.'' &QL; 
41.`` Diary of a Lost Girl'' (1929) G.W. Pabst _ Silent film is a
sordid Louise Brooks vehicle. &QL; 
42.`` The Sorrow and the Pity'' (1970) Marcel Ophuls _ Are the Nazi
collaborators telling the truth? Documentary. &QL; 
43.`` La Bete Humaine'' (1938) Renoir _ Jean Gabin is a train
engineer who witnesses a murder. &QL; 
44.`` Andalusian Dog'' (1928) Bunuel _ Surrealist flagship film. &QL; 
45.`` Diabolique'' (1955) Henri-Georges Clouzot _ Is the murder
victim dead? Forget Sharon Stone; rent this. &QL; 
46.`` A Nous la Liberte'' (1931) Rene Clair _ ``Modern Times'' in
French. &QL; 
47.`` M.'' (1931) Lang _ Criminals convict a child molester. &QL; 
48.`` Ivan the Terrible Parts 1&AMP;2'' (1943-1946) Eisenstein _
Once-banned pageant, too close to home for Stalin. &QL; 
49.`` Henry V'' (1945) Laurence Olivier _ Shakespeare's
theatricality apotheosized. Is it stage or cinema? &QL; 
50.`` Woman in the Dunes'' (1964) Hiroshi Teshigahara _ Japanese
vacationer gets caught in sand trap of life. &QL; 
51.`` Mr. Hulot's Holiday'' (1953) Jacques Tati _ Comic seaside
vacation. Tati's best film. &QL; 
52.`` Hiroshima Mon Amour'' (1959) Alain Resnais _ Interracial love
and angst in post-war Japan, told stream-of-consciousness. &QL; 
53. ``Aguirre, Wrath of God'' (1972) Werner Herzog _ Klaus Kinski
as a Spaniard, leading doomed expedition down Amazon. &QL; 
54.`` Last Tango in Paris'' (1973) Bertolucci _ Brando laments dead
wife, has nameless affair with young woman. &QL; 
55. ``Smiles of a Summer Night'' (1955) Bergman _ Drawing-room
comedy matches the lovers with correct mates. &QL; 
56.`` Wild Child'' (1969) Truffaut _ Science vs. Parenthood. &QL; 
57.`` Farewell My Concubine'' (1993) Chen Kaige _ Chinese opera vs.
Maoism. A film with broad sweep. &QL; 
58.`` Olympia'' (1936) Leni Riefenstahl _ Athletics as heroism. &QL; 
59. ``The Gospel According to St. Matthew'' (1966) Pier Paolo
Pasolini _ Sober replay of Bible story, told absolutely straight. &QL; 
60.`` Hara Kiri'' (1962) Masaki Kobayashi _ Harrowing samurai
revenge epic. &QL; 
61.`` The Mahabharata'' (1989) Peter Brook _ Theatrical film tells
history of the world, Vedic-style. &QL; 
62.`` Shop on Main Street'' (1965) Jan Kadar _ Subverting Nazis in
Czechoslovakia. &QL; 
63.`` Pauline at the Beach'' (1983) Eric Rohmer _ Urbane French
parable about adult hypocrisy. &QL; 
64.`` The Wages of Fear'' (1952) Clouzot _ Explosive road movie. &QL; 
65``. Der Golem'' (1920) Paul Wegener _ Silent progenitor of
Frankenstein examines Jewish ghetto life. That's right. &QL; 
66.`` Fellini Satyricon'' (1970) Fellini _ If you thought the
Classics were dull, you've underestimated Fellini. &QL; 
67. ``The Virgin Spring'' (1959) Bergman _ Medieval folk tale. &QL; 
68.`` Discreet Charm of the Bourgeoisie'' (1972) Bunuel _ Let's do
lunch, in hell. Recast of Tantalus myth. &QL; 
69. ``Scenes from a Marriage'' (1973) Bergman _ Very civilized
divorce. Very definition of ``internalization.'' &QL; 
70.`` The Passenger'' (1975) Antonioni _ Jack Nicholson in Italian
art film, changes identities, risks life. &QL; 
71.`` Beauty and the Beast'' (1946) Cocteau _ Magical retelling of
fairy tale. Puts Disney to shame. &QL; 
72``. Last Year at Marienbad'' (1961) Resnais _ Classic puzzle
picture. Don't believe anything you see. &QL; 
73``. The Baker's Wife'' (1938) Marcel Pagnol _ She ran away, but
the town still needs bread. &QL; 
74.`` Nibelungenlied Parts 1&AMP;2: Siegfried and Kriemhild's
Revenge.'' (1924) Lang _ German saga brilliantly remounted. &QL; 
75.`` Knife in the Water'' (1962) Roman Polanski _ Thriller. Don't
pick up hitchhikers. &QL; 
76.`` Small Change'' (1976) Truffaut _ One of the few films about
childhood that isn't sappy. &QL; 
77. ``The Hidden Fortress'' (1958) Kurosawa _ C-3PO and R2D2 help
princess in Medieval Japan. &QL; 
78``. The Magician'' (1958) Bergman _ Science vs. Religion. &QL; 
79. ``The Mystery of Picasso'' (1956) Clouzot _ Documentary of
great painter at work. Utter magic. &QL; 
80.`` Maedchen in Uniform'' (1931) Leontine Sagan _ Touching,
tender story of leather, Nazis and lesbians. &QL; 
81.`` Every Man for Himself and God Against All'' (1975) Herzog _
Hypnotic story of a mysterious stranger. &QL; 
82.`` Salaam Bombay'' (1988) Mira Nair _ Street life in India. &QL; 
83. ``Stolen Kisses'' (1968) Truffaut _ Antoine Doinel, from`` 400
Blows,'' grows up, sort of. &QL; 
84``. Los Olvidados'' (1950) Bunuel _ Street life in Mexico. &QL; 
85.`` Black Orpheus'' (1959) Marcel Camus _ Myth retold in Brazil,
with song and samba. &QL; 
86.`` Autumn Sonata'' (1978) Bergman _ Quintessential
mother-daughter film, complete with icy stares. &QL; 
87.`` 39 Steps'' (1935) Alfred Hitchcock _ Spies and McGuffins from
the master of suspense. &QL; 
88. ``Throne of Blood'' (1957) Kurosawa _ Japanese Macbeth. &QL; 
89.`` Yojimbo'' (1961) Kurosawa _ Samurai ``Fistful of Dollars.'' &QL; 
90.`` Sanjuro'' (1962) Kurosawa _ Another ``Teriyaki Western.'' &QL; 
91.`` Pather Panchali'' (1955) Satyajit Ray _ Poor family raises
son in poverty-stricken Bengal. &QL; 
92.`` Arabian Nights'' (1974) Pasolini _ Scheherezade in the nude.
Simple filmmaking, complex storytelling. &QL; 
93.`` The Story of Adele H.'' (1975) Truffaut _ Touching portrait
of obsessive love. With Isabelle Adjani. &QL; 
94.`` Loneliness of the Long Distance Runner'' (1962) Tony
Richardson _ Borstal boy throws race, finds manhood. &QL; 
95.`` The Devil's Eye'' (1960) Bergman _ Don Juan comes back from
hell to seduce preacher's daughter. &QL; 
96.`` Forbidden Quest'' (1995) Peter Delpeut _ Visionary Antarctic
pseudo-documentary. &QL; 
97.`` Bye-bye Brazil'' (1980) Carlos Diegues _ Roaming Brazil's
back country with traveling magic show. &QL; 
98. ``The Passion of Anna'' (1969) Bergman _ Isolation and love on
a Swedish island. In color, though hard to tell. &QL; 
99.`` Akira Kurosawa's Dreams'' (1990) Kurosawa _ Uneven anthology,
but the best episodes are visionary. &QL; 
100.`` Marat/Sade'' (1966) Brook _ The persecution and
assassination of Jean-Paul Marat as performed by the inmates of the
asylum at Charenton under the direction of the Marquis de Sade. In
English. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
